        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 5:32PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 532 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles east of Amarillo, moving north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Amarillo, Claude, Washburn, and Pantex.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
